# Testing Rule (Vitest/Jest)

## Test Strategy

- Prefer fast unit tests for core business logic.
- Add integration tests at system boundaries (DB, message bus, external APIs).
- Add contract tests for request/response schemas and error envelopes.
- Cover success, failure, and edge-case behavior.

## Test Quality

- One behavior per test; use clear Arrange/Act/Assert structure.
- Use descriptive test names that explain expected behavior.
- Avoid brittle assertions tied to implementation details.
- Use deterministic data and fixed clocks/random seeds.

## Mocks and Fakes

- Mock only external boundaries; avoid mocking the unit under test.
- Prefer lightweight fakes/stubs over heavy global mocks.
- Reset mock state between tests.
- Keep mock behavior realistic for critical paths.

## Async and Time

- Always await async operations and assertions.
- Use fake timers only when needed and restore after each test.
- Validate timeout/retry paths explicitly when they affect behavior.

## Coverage Expectations

- Treat coverage as a signal, not the goal.
- Ensure changed code paths are tested before merge.
- Add regression tests for every fixed bug.
- Maintain high confidence in auth, billing, and data-mutation paths.

## Tooling Notes

- Vitest preferred for modern TS ESM workflows unless project dictates Jest.
- Keep setup files minimal and explicit.
- Avoid shared mutable global fixtures across test files.

